The paper deals with the problem of testing for forbidden order patterns in sequences, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and has connections to various subfields such as data structures, computational complexity, information theory, discrete mathematics, and computational geometry. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under several sub-categories, with cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) being the most likely ones, followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
